===Etymology 2===
{{defdate|circa 1680}} From [[sashes]], from {{etyl|fr|en}} {{m|fr|châssis||frame (of a window or door)}}, taken as a plural and -s trimmed off by the late 17th century.<ref>Attested in 1684 in {{w|Aphra Behn}}, ''{{w|Love-Letters Between a Nobleman and His Sister}}''.<sup>[http://name.umdl.umich.edu/A27301.0001.001]</sup></ref> See also [[chassis]].
